The dictionary, however it was produced does not use #34, the short &quot;o&quot; 
sound, which Read illustrated with the word &quot;O-x.&quot;  It should appear in 
words such as &quot;hot,&quot; &quot;pot&quot;, &quot;hobby,&quot; &quot;stocky,&quot; etc.  The long &quot;A-h&quot; 
sound (#32), instead, is used throughout this dictionary. Examples:  
&quot;father,&quot; &quot;calm.&quot; &quot;alarm.&quot;  This is a longer vowel and should not be 
mistaken for #34.

Paige

